Danish Danisco appoints new chief exec . Danish food and drinks group Danisco A / S on Tuesday appointed Alf Duch - Pedersen as new chief executive to succeed outgoing Palle Marcus effective April 1 , 1997 . It said in a statement that Marcus had decided to take up his contractual option to retire on his 60th birthday and planned to assume a number of posts on other company boards . Duch - Pedersen , 50 , takes over his new Danisco CEO post after five years as president and chief executive of Denmark ' s leading Tryg - Baltica insurance group . - - Chris Follett , Copenhagen newsroom + 45 - 33969652 
